From 386aa637f39ac6c8026459a74a3de714489142c4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Scott Chacon <schacon@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 21:04:47 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 8/624] Work in /Users/schacon/projects/gust.

**Goal:** Make `tests/t1400-update-ref.sh` pass (all cases).

Read the test file and implement/fix `gust/src/commands/update_ref.rs` plus `gust-lib` ref helpers if needed.

Known failure themes from runs:
- Stale old-value must block delete
- `git update-ref HEAD` should dereference symbolic HEAD to current branch ref (tests use `cat .git/HEAD` vs branch tip — fix path handling; avoid `cat .git/` directory errors)
- `--stdin` must accept empty input (no-op success)
- Stdin update with **zero** old-value (`0{40}`) to create ref
- Transaction batch: `start` / `create` / `commit` commands (see git update-ref batch format)

**Constraints:** `cargo fmt`, `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings`, `cargo test --workspace`. Run `cd tests && GUST_BIN=.../target/debug/gust sh ./t1400-update-ref.sh` until green.

Do NOT edit plan.md/progress.md. Do NOT commit.

Return: summary and files changed.

- Fixed `update-ref -d <ref> <old>` to validate the correct old-value positional argument so stale old-values block deletion.
- Added HEAD dereference behavior (unless `--no-deref`) so updating `HEAD` writes to its symbolic target branch ref.
- Implemented zero-old-value (`000...0`) semantics for update/verify/delete checks so update with zero old-value can create missing refs.
- Added `--stdin` transaction support for `start`/`commit` with queued operations and required status output (`start: ok`, `commit: ok`).
- Kept empty `--stdin` input as no-op success and refactored batch op execution paths for consistency.
